    <li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#menu2"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-download-alt logo-medium"></span><br>Download</a></li>
    <li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#menu3"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-blackboard logo-medium"></span><br>Gallery</a></li>
  </ul>




  <div class="tab-content">
    <div id="home" class="tab-pane fade in active">
      <div id="tutorial" class="container-fluid bg-grey" align="left">
      <h3>Dosematic is...</h3>
      <ul>
	<li>User friendly graphical interface.</li>
	<li>Tool for a conveinent data input.</li>
	<li>Fits calibration curve to entered data.</li>
	<li>Calculates yields, doses and their statistical uncertainties.</li>
	<li>Suitable for three exposure modes: Acute, Partial and Protracted.</li>
	<li>Covers five data categories: Dicentric Assay, DNA Repair Foci, Micronucleus Assay, FISH Translocation, PCC Chemically Induced and PCC Fusion.</li>
      <ul>
    </div>
    <div class="container-fluid bg-grey" align="left">
      <p>See for yourself -- check out our <a class="link-to-tab" href="#menu3"><button class="btn btn-default btn-sm"></span>Gallery</button></a><br>
      Or go straight to the <a class="link-to-tab" href="#menu2"><button class="btn btn-default btn-sm"></span>Download page</button></a><br>
      For an easy start with the DoseMatic platform check out our <a class="link-to-tab" href="#menu1"><button class="btn btn-default btn-sm"></span>Guides</button></a><br>
    </div>
    </div>





